sentences: Frances Wolff (March 4, 1926 – March 4, 2013), known professionally as Fran Warren, was an American singer.
She spent almost two years with the Charlie Barnet band before achieving some recognition with Claude Thornhill.
In 1947, she reached the music charts for the first time with the song "A Sunday Kind of Love" written by her manager, Barbara Belle.
During the same year, she sang on the radio program Sing It Again.
